Who would’ve thought that 17 years after I first joined the Top Chef world I would still be booking and executing culinary demos with and for my amazing Top Chef family?! What an honor and privilege. Now, 17 years later, my catering company, @ryanscott2go is beyond in full bloom, and it’s the best it’s ever been. From soup to nuts, we do it all. With my incredible kitchen staff, service team, and my executive assistant, Dana Baker, we curate, and bring to fruition the best in culinary experiences and events. Our innovative food-service styles, custom written menus, a focus on local and sustainable ingredients, and a client-centered approach have allowed us to gain the trust of the greater Bay Area community and beyond when it comes to exquisite catered events. It’s our simultaneous ability to keep the larger picture AND tiny details in tandem focus that ensures our clients feel the RS2go love from beginning to end. We are proud to say that we are booked through Fall of 2025 with new and long-time clients because of our passion, love, and respect for the culinary arts, and the procurement of exceptional client experiences.

I would not be honoring my brother, Wes @goweser if I didn’t just say how I’m feeling today….. I would like to just say that this page is for everybody, if I offend you because I love ALL, it’s very easy to not be offended by me:) I literally love everybody and we are some damn lucky fools to be on this earth for such a short time…. I can only imagine what we could get done if hate wasn’t in the way. I hope that everybody has a fabulous 🫰🏻weekend and understands that the best gift tomorrow is the fact that we opened our eyes…..

This year marks 30 years that I’ve been cooking behind a stove… my parents had a diner when we were in middle school and I became the cheapest short order line cook ever🤣, #rollsofquarters #streetfighter #pizzahut #losbanos for the win…. 

I’m saying this, because yesterday I had a moment, a moment of calmness, a moment of appreciation for just a little while. I was in my my zone of culinary Disneyland … cooking at this wood fired stove yesterday at @aristawinery brought me such a joy and happiness. I was also reminded of the force and power that comes with #livefirecooking…. 

Funny how this little fire yesterday, stoked a new fire of happiness, love and appreciation for the art of food🫰🏻 which has consumed me for over 85% of my life. 

Have a bless Sunday, hope you find your fire today… 

Xoxo
Rye

My heart lead me down by the Golden Gate bridge and I took a moment for me, it made me realize that we have Christmas every single say..To hug & kiss & see my wife in the morning! that’s a gift. To hear my kids laugh and run up stairs at 6am, that’s a gift. Every morning when I reach into my fridge, not worrying if we have food or not, that’s a gift…. 

I’ve lived in the bay area for 22 years and call it home, this is my first time to this spot ever, im beyond blessed to have a moment of gratitude, that my family and friends❤️ is a gift…

For almost 20yrs I’ve wanted to honor our sister Melany that we lost over 20yrs ago.. For many, many, many years old management would say NO! Ryan you’re such a clean/special brand and you’ll lose so much endorsements by doing that, TV will hate you, I’ll never be able to book you again…( by the way not my amazing manager that’s been with me for a while @mrtimkessler, you rock)

Guess what, at 43 and loads of mental struggles, I finally have allowed myself to be me, I stopped, trying to fit in the square box of television( morning television) and I finally allowed myself to be me.. we have such a small moment on this earth, I finally I’m going be me. I let so many people dictate all of moves, when to fly, when to smile, when to post, when not to be home to celebrate holidays just for a stupid two minute segment... Well this year I celebrate my 30th year in culinary arts, and the only mold that I’m going to fit, is mine… I have two Emmys on my mantle, two best selling books, my catering company is the strongest it’s ever been on its 18th year and I’m about to release the two most amazing projects, seriously the best I’ve ever done in my whole life. TY @catherinecoydesign🫰🏻,long story short, I’m in charge of this book called Ryan, and if you judge it, move on🖕🏻 if you’re wondering, what’s the sunflower on my elbow,  it’s for Wes @goweser! The flower that stands for loyalty, adoration, positivity and strength, boy oh boy Wes! did you leave a fucking gap in my heart…For the first time in my life, when I’m having a shitty day, I just looked on my arm, and I see my daughters( Olives and Poppies), my sister Mel and our lovely, gorgeous Wes, and I’m good & instantly reset. And for the record, I was having trouble finding the proper butterflies…. The night before I was gonna see my tattoo artist, poppy jumped on my lap for me to put her to bed, and she was wearing butterfly pajamas, and that’s exactly what’s on my arm( I heard you Mel, thanks for giving me direction)

I am beyond excited to write my own book finally, the unedited Ryan:)

I’m in the peek of 2009, I had a rockstar cooking show #foodrush, my own radio show on @kgoradio ( which Michael, listen to, would call in often and was on at least a half a dozen times) for 9.5yrs & two restaurants… there’s two BEYOND giant things that stand out with @chefchiarello… also a million more..

this video is a snapshot of him and I shooting one of the episodes of food rush together … 

The other moment that didn’t have any cameras( thank GOD), is when I was dining at coqueta with friends, I get a telephone call that I was nominated for my first #emmy, Michael comes over and gives me the biggest hug, pours wine down my throat and whispers in my ear, I love you, Ryan, but I got a couple more Emmys than you:)

I’ve literally haven’t been able to do anything the last three days.. All I’ve been doing is watch reruns of Napa style , reread his cookbooks four times, and thanked the universe for our friendship… 

Love you MC my Central Valley brother

P.S nobody knows this, but in 2008, 2009, Michael personally called the food network @bobtuschman, and asked to have a meeting with me.. this was and still is a giant moment for me . Food TV/competition sometimes is something people don’t like share the camera or spot light( & still is) or get crazy jealous about someone stealing there thunder. Michael couldn’t give two shits, he told me you deserve to be on TV and I wanna get you in front of everybody including Bob Tuschman… not only did he do that, but he did more, and forever thankful.
#dropthemic

When I started building my passion project for @ryanscott2go , my number one goal was to work with self owned  business operators., and people that actually work and ran their business.. I’ve not been let down from @mmbbqcompany and now @centralcoastwoodfiredovens and owner operator Guillermo.. From day one he’s called me back in less than 1 hour, meet me in person, gave me all the pros and cons, told me because of my height that we should raise my pizza oven, Guillermo even found the specialty tile which is my daughters favorite colors and mine… 

if you’re even thinking about a Pizza Oven! Guillermo is your man! I Family guy, build’s his ovens from scratch, and he shows up…. Did you all hear me? this man shows up! 

I can’t wait to do more work with  @centralcoastwoodfiredovens

In a couple weeks I’m turning 44 and I’m so honored to still have my parents to lean on, emotionally and physically… my beautiful wife has been on a work trip for a week and my parents helped me out with the girls & more… 

An extra big shout of to my Dad Danny for coming through and driving my diesel’s & crew to a couple events that I couldn’t be at… #famshoutout @ryanscott2go

Wrap up to another amazing week. I am really proud of my team because my food experiences are not just about food. They are about laughter, music, tons of booze, and reminding us why time together is so special today.  We have two open spots for a #ryanscott2go over the top Christmas event!

Love you @heyitschasedaley for always making the best content ever!
